Incident.Summary: Probable cause search of the vehicle resulting in CDS, not marijuana.

IncidentSuppNarrative.NarrativeText: Maryland State Police Princess Anne Barrack X Tpr. J. D. Revel III, IBM 7146 Field Operation Bureau February 8th, 2023 Maryland State Police Patrol Vehicle:X-11 is a maroon unmarked 2021 Ford Explorer equipped with MVR system. Type of Report:Possession of CDS, Not Marijuana Driver/Defendant:Nephtalie Daniel Moise Date of Birth: 8/29/2001 Criminal Citation Number:172004405834 CDS PH Number:P-341702 Troopers Training/Experience: * Trained in administering Standardized Field Sobriety Tests through the Maryland State Police and National Highway Traffic Safety Administration (NHTSA). * Trained and certified to operate Radar and LiDAR through the Maryland State Police. * NHTSA certified in Advanced Roadside Impaired Driving Enforcement (A.R.I.D.E). * Attended numerousNHTSA certified cannabis impairment detection workshops. * Federal Motor Carrier Safety Administration (FMCSA) certified commercial vehicle weights officer. * FMCSA certified North American Standard (NAS) Level III Commercial Vehicle Inspector. * Attended the 2021 Middle Atlantic-Great Lakes Organized Crime Law Enforcement Network (MAGLOCLEN) Conference. * Certified At-Scene (Level I) Crash Reconstructionist through the Baltimore County Police Department and Maryland Crash Reconstruction Committee (MCRC). * Certified in Advanced (Level II) Crash Investigation through the Montgomery County Police Department and Maryland Crash Reconstruction Committee (MCRC). * Attended the 2022 Maryland Impaired Driving Conference hosted by the Maryland Department of Transportation and Zero Deaths Maryland. * Trained in Human Trafficking investigation and recovery through the Federal Bureau of Investigation and the Maryland State Police. * Certified Standardized Field Sobriety Instructor through the Maryland State Police. Scene Processing: CDS Seized: 4x THC Oil Cartridges (Schedule I CDS) Narrative: This report has been prepared based upon the observations of this trooper and/or those of other troopers relative to the offense(s). The facts contained herein are intended solely to give the prosecuting authority a basic understanding of the facts pertaining to this case. The facts contained herein are not intended to be an exhaustive recitation of the facts pertaining to pretrial or trial issues. Instead, this trooper anticipates that during the pretrial proceedings in this case, the prosecutor will take the opportunity to interview this trooper in order to ascertain any and all relevant facts which might be the subject of this troopers testimony during court proceedings. On February 8th, 2023, I was conducting speed enforcing as a part of a stopping team on US Route 13 at Short Lane in Westover, Somerset County, Maryland. At approximately 1533 hours, I observed a gray Honda Accord that appeared to traveling over the posted speed limit of 55 miles per hour. I measured the vehicles speed with laser and received a digital speed reading of 78 miles per hour at a distance of 1554.1 feet. I directed the vehicle to the center the median to conduct a traffic stop. As the vehicle was rolling to a stop, I observed the driver fumbling around in the vehicle. As I approached the window, I noticed that the driver, completely unaware that I was already at the window, was spraying an odor masking agent around the passenger compartment of the vehicle. As soon as the driver noticed I was there, she rolled down the window. As she did, I immediately detected the strong and distinct odor of marijuana. I told the driver who I was, the reason for the stop, and that they were being audibly and visually recorded. I was then handed a Maryland Drivers License where I was able to further identify the driver as Nephtalie Daniel Moise (DOB: 8/29/2001). A probable cause search of the vehicle was conducted. In the center console of the vehicle, I located the following: - One (1) Nova brand Strawberry Splash THC Oil cartridge - One (1) Nova brand Ice Cream Sorbet THC Oil cartridge - Two (2) Flyy brand Blue Dream THC Oil cartridges No further contraband was found. Based on my training, knowledge, and experience as a Maryland State Trooper, I identified the substance found in the vehicle as Tetrahydrocannabinol Oil, Schedule I CDS, not marijuana. Moise was issued a Maryland Traffic Citation for exceeding the posted speed limit and a uniform criminal citation for possession of CDS, not marijuana. Moise was released from the scene without further incident. The evidence was seized, packaged, and documented per MSP policy and placed into the evidence drop-box at the Princess Anne Barrack. Based on the above facts, I request the case be CLOSED, criminal citation issued. All events occurred in Somerset County, Maryland.
